<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-251] Content-Length &amp; Transfer-Encoding request headers should be handled by entity enclosing methods</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-251</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Currently &amp;#39;Content-Length&amp;#39; &amp;amp; &amp;#39;Transfer-Encoding&amp;#39; request headers are handled by &lt;br/&gt;
the HttpMethodBase class. This is conceptually wrong and error-prone in my &lt;br/&gt;
opinion. Entity enclosing methods should control &amp;#39;Content-Length&amp;#39; &amp;amp; &amp;#39;Transfer-&lt;br/&gt;
Encoding&amp;#39; request headers instead, as they provide request content and &lt;br/&gt;
encapsulate the requisite content transfer logic.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
